The driver lost control of the bus and then crashed into two houses in Nyanga East on Saturday afternoon. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town police are investigating after a Golden Arrow bus driver was shot and killed while at the wheel. The driver lost control of the bus and then crashed into two houses in Nyanga East on Saturday afternoon. It’s unclear whether the shooter had been on board the bus or had fired at the vehicle from the street. The police’s Andre Traut says no other injuries were reported. “Fortunately, no one else was injured and no arrests have been made.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)